The paper deals with the calculation of mutual information for communication channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It specifically focuses on partially coherent channels, which are commonly found in fiber optics (cs.OH, cs.PH). The paper also discusses the effects of nonlinearities in fiber-optic channels, which is a topic in nonlinear optics (cs.NI). Finally, the paper uses numerical simulations and analytical expressions, which are common tools in computational mathematics (cs.MM).
